<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-09-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-09-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="529" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d529">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hill</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hart</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-09-08"><hi rend="italic">September 8,
                                    1900</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Hill directs Mr. Hart to notify the new Government of his readiness
                            to enter into relations when it is in possession of the machinery of
                            administration, is maintaining order, executing the laws of Colombia
                            with the general assent of the people, and responsibly fulfilling
                            international obligations.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>